<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8323966>
    dc:description "FIGURE 31. Indohya cribbi Harvey & Burger, n. sp.: A–C, holotype male (WAM T138721): A, dorsal; B, ventral; C, cephalothorax, dorsal; D–F, paratype female (WAM T138717): D, dorsal; E, ventral; F, cephalothorax, dorsal. Scale lines = 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8323966/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8323970>
    dc:description "FIGURE 32. Indohya cribbi Harvey & Burger, n. sp., holotype male (WAM T138721), unless stated otherwise: A, carapace, dorsal; B, right pedipalp, dorsal; C, left chela, retrolateral; D, left chelal teeth, retrolateral; E, left chela, retrolateral, tritonymph (WAM T150970); F, left chela, retrolateral, protonymph (WAM T138974). Scale lines = 0.5 mm (Figs. B, C), 0.25 mm (Figs. E, F), 0.2 mm (Fig. D), 0.1 mm (Fig. A)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8323970/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

